# Stacking tool preference

This is the **in-repo agent SSOT** for stacking (replaces any retired `docs/GRAPHITE.md`).

Before creating branches or submitting/restacking PRs, **read** `.github/stacking-tool`
(single line: `graphite` or `gh-stack`). Missing or invalid values: **stop and ask** —
do not guess.

## `gh-stack` (this repo)

Canonical playbook (do not invent flags):

- Local: `~/work/ai/repository-helpers/.cursor/skills/gh-stack/SKILL.md`
- GitHub: https://github.com/the-hcma/repository-helpers/blob/main/.cursor/skills/gh-stack/SKILL.md
- Thin local pointer: `.cursor/skills/gh-stack/SKILL.md`

Prefer `~/work/ai/repository-helpers/scripts/dev/submit-stack` /
`ship-and-review` (they dispatch via `scripts/lib/stacking-tool`).

**Do not** mix with `gt create` / `gt submit` / `gt restack` on the same stack.

Human-oriented cheat sheet: `docs/GH-STACK.md`.

## `graphite`

Not used in this repository. If the marker is ever `graphite`, follow
`~/work/ai/repository-helpers/.cursor/skills/graphite/SKILL.md` and `gt` via
`submit-stack`.

## Unchanged regardless of marker

Agent review, CI wait, and reply-before-resolve still follow
`.cursor/rules/pr-ship-and-review.mdc` and the repository-helpers ship-and-review Skill.
